column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: -Clear with ice on shoreline in spots. Not affecting flow. Some trees observed floating down and hung up on shallow areas.
column14: -M9 measurement from boat with trimaran. ~800m upstream of gauge. -MGH from telemetry, USB not available for download. -Shift value is larger than found in 2023 but in line with 2020-2022 shift values. -@ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken at usual spot under helipad at bottom of path from gauge. -Bubbler offset 3.019 / OTT offset -0.189 -HG2 is feeding NG signal. -These levels seem to confirm a reading error of the cut on the last levels in April, which was expected to be found. They should be discarded and these levels carried back to the previous SRC. -Orifice movement occured on HG2 resulting the large SRC. -No download. USB not available.  ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: 4.165 HG2: 3.609 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  Reset (RS)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Calm Wind Blowing Upstream
column13:
-Ice cover with overflow. 
-Some overflow has eroded snow on river upstream of gauge showing pooling and appears to be completely open narrow sections downstream ~500m.
column14: -StreamPro measurement ~0.8km upstream, just above the bend and in similar location to February measurement. -~0.2m overflow on ice over fastest sections, and less over the slow section mid transect. -MGH taken from HG2 as OTT will be the data source for FEB to APR (on onwards) stage. -Average of 5 minute MGH values on Field review page, steady through mmt. Mean time entered as no change from average. @ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken at usual spot at base of path from gauge to benchmarks. -No hole drilled due to excessive amount of overflow and observation that it is in no way draining after a hole drilled at measurement section nearby. Usual approach here in late winter/spring. -OTT did not previously have offset applied. Mid-section
HG: 3.872 HG2: 3.317 Surge: 0.000  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Calm Wind Blowing Downstream
column13:
-Complete ice cover entire visible reach of river.
-snow deep on channel but anecdotally not as deep as usual.
column14: -Ice surface mmt with StreamPro, ~500m upstream of gauge, ~100m upstream of bend. -New location to try and avoid occasional issue of eddy's at traditional winter location. Seem to have picked up issue of large panhandle profile but otherwise a reasonable spot. -MGH from OTT on HG2. -@ Uncertainty: ISO method, 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -DWL at bottom of path from gauge - usual spot -No reset or re-programming. No time to run confirmation levels. -SDL32 couldnt read barcode as it was moving too much. Used as conventional. -RFT note: current source of stage is telemetry.2 (OTT sub). Offset currently 0.554. I will look at the best way to correct coming to the visit. Please apply SRC from HG2 forward (0.533) Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Moderate Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: -Clear of ice. Some debris running in main flow but nothing substantial observed, just small logs.
column14: -Manned boat mmt with M9 in trimaran -Originally tried at heli landing spot but strong upstream wind and low edge velocities made for poorly correlated transects (6 collected) -ignored those six and tried ~300m D/S, much better results. 4 transects and loop from this location used. -MB present. GPS not available so correction applied. -@ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken in line with BM. -No obvious mark for high water but given saturated ground between BM and water, assume it was higher. -Offset: 3.028 ADCP by Moving Boat
